					<p>I also had the same problem with the RSS feeds as Lucian Lature had.  The named parameters are not coming through correctly.  I was still able to get to the articles properly by manually editing the URLs as follows:</p>
<p><a rel="nofollow" href="http://debuggable.com/posts/48d2112f-53b4-4a15-b6c5-5d5f4834cda3">http://debuggable.com/posts/48d2112f-53b4-4a15-b6c5-5d5f4834cda3</a><br />
to</br><br />
<a rel="nofollow" href="http://debuggable.com/posts/anything:48d2112f-53b4-4a15-b6c5-5d5f4834cda3">http://debuggable.com/posts/anything:48d2112f-53b4-4a15-b6c5-5d5f4834cda3</a></br></p>
<p>The addition of a name for the parameter (I just used a single letter) caused the site to do a proper lookup for each article and changed the URL appropriately.</p>
<p>HTH someone...</p>
<p>In case such a thing ever happens again, Felix or Tim or whoever writes the code for this blog should maybe have the Posts controller do a lookup on the article based on the UUID if a bare UUID is passed instead of a named parameter UUID so that the problem is automagically fixed on the fly.</p>
